As the day went by the enemy got larger. Should have been easier, I implied. Being responsible and wisely driving, I reduced the speed and distance between my car and his so it would not shock the man any further. He didn’t speak very much and I understand. A diesel truck most likely in the US. He didn’t sign registration of the cars. As I finally reached the bus, I asked him how much money he has. He pulled out a 50 lei micro and a 50 lei note. My eyes sized them and I was about to tell him “No more too much money”. The way I was predisposed to deal with people had formed a certain view of some kind of attitude. I had become a critical person who doesn’t give anything to anyone. But I knew he was sick. And after riding for some time I gave him the entire money in Ukrainian hryvna which was about 35 euros. He was surprised of receiving something at all and first didn’t want to accept it. I must say he looked like he had severe mental problems. His distance from society could have had several causes.
